net.sourceforge.reb4j
Class CharClass

java.lang.Object
  net.sourceforge.reb4j.Regex
      net.sourceforge.reb4j.CharClass
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class CharClass
extends Regex

Specialization of Regex representing a character class expression. Because character classes can be composed of other character classes (but not other type of regular expressions), a separate CharClass class is needed in order to distinguish character classes from other types of regular expressions. This facilitates the creation of methods representing operations specific to character classes.

Author:
Richard W. Eggert II

Method Detail

characters

public static CharClass characters(CharSequence characters,
                                   boolean negate)
Creates a CharClass that matches any of the specified characters, or if negate is true, any character except those specified. This method automatically escapes all characters that need escaping.

Parameters:
characters - the set of characters to match.
negate - if true, the returned CharClass will match any character EXCEPT those specified by characters; otherwise, only the specified characters will match.
Returns:
a CharClass matching the specified characters or their inverse set.
Throws:
NullPointerException - if characters is null.

characters

public static CharClass characters(CharSequence characters)
Creates a CharClass that matches any of the specified characters. This method is equivalent to calling characters(characters, false).

Parameters:
characters - the set of characters to match.
Returns:
a CharClass matching the specified characters.
Throws:
NullPointerException - if characters is null.

union

public static CharClass union(CharClass... operands)
Constructs a CharClass representing the union of all the specified CharClasses.

intersection

public static CharClass intersection(CharClass... operands)
Constructs a CharClass representing the intersection of all the specified character classes.

Parameters:
operands - the character classes to intersect.
Returns:
a CharClass that matches only those characters that are are matched by ALL character classes specified by operands.

range

public static CharClass range(char first,
                              char last,
                              boolean negate)
Constructs a character class representing a range of characters or its inverse. This method automatically escapes all characters that need escaping.

Parameters:
first - the first character in the range.
last - the last character in the range.
negate - if true, the returned CharClass will match all characters EXCEPT those in the specified range; if false, the returned CharClass will match only those characters in the specified range.
Returns:
a CharClass matching all character values between first and last, inclusive, or the inverse of that (if negate is true).

range

public static CharClass range(char first,
                              char last)
Constructs a character class representing a range of characters. This method is equivalent to calling range(first, last, false).

Parameters:
first - the first character in the range.
last - the last character in the range.
Returns:
a CharClass matching all character values between first and last, inclusive.
See Also:
range(char, char, boolean)
